 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uwilrowe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wilrowe</A> at: 1/31/02 9:57:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udekeeverburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deke Everburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/31/02 9:57:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1659.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dragonsong.org/graphics/deke.jpg height=130 width=173></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Love for Mages...NOT</span><hr size=1>    Hehe, ok about dire charm yes it works GREAT and I am not asking for them to nerf it... I sat in Arena with someone with Dire charm for an extended period of time... yes he could solo there if he wanted, trust me.  Why would I want them to nerf something that works well, because Im pissed about my class?  Thats kinda lame don't you think?  I mean he HAD to do some work to get the skill right?  So why decide to screw him for working hard to get it?<br>
   <br>
   About mage epic being bagged... uhm well the nice thing about our epic is you don't have to have the thing in your hand to get the effect... Just summon your pet and destroy your summoned skittle stick if you want.  So you have something better to use, summon pet, skittle stick destroy, gtg.  I don't quite understand how you could EVER find something to make you bag that, being as the lvl 60 water pet is not like an epic pet and that is the effect on epic.  Sure you may not have the thing equipped but we don't need it equipped. <br>
   <br>
   About nukes, yes we are second best nuking power, problem with it is, the master of elements, shouldn't we at least be able to use all elements?  Not just fire and magic... I mean maybe a DS like our fire line that uses cold instead and adds to cold resist, and a cold nuke or two.  BTW, something I enjoy from luclin... the summoned elemental blankets and defenders.  If your with a raid party that isn't exactly perfect on resists and have a mage along, you can get summoned resists. Now those are decent, and can be used everywhere.     <br>
   <br>
   I just get tired of seeing everyone thinking every mage is just whining up a river about there class, don't you think if it bugged me enough I would have quit my class long ago... I like Deke and deal with shit as it works out... Doesnt mean I am not allowed to express a wish along with others for a change, right?  I know mages are not the only ones to get the shaft, I agree MANY classes still need improvements for a perfectly "class-balanced" world. <br>
   <br>
   IMO whoever the guy was that was doing the questioning (my apologies if your on this server) was looking for something to start shit with and got the answers he was looking for.  If you approach someone picking a fight and don't expect them to try and discourage you, your a fool.<br>
   <br>
   Class balancing sucks, deal or start over.<br>
<br>
   *EDIT* Edeina, may wanna kick this to nag.<br>
