</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uycorerixle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ycorerixle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/31/02 10:19:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1659.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/ycore?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Love for Mages...NOT</span><hr size=1> Actually, necro pets will do more dmg then the standard mage greater Vocerate pets.  Why?  They don't spend combat rounds casting highly resistable 100dmg nukes or roots, they PROC their lifetap once in awhile instead.  The main thing that makes mage pets superior is that they can actually tank for a bit if they have too. Necro pets get beaten down mighty fast if they have to tank.  Problem is, except in a solo situation pets no longer CAN tank since they have NO aggro if there is a single PC within combat range.<br>
<br>
  As for upgrading the Epic pet, I agree it isn't necessary--and isn't where Verant should give mages more power, if any. IMHO classes should be balanced based upon their NATURAL abilities, not by whatever extra perks they get from their Epic.  Most mages will never get their epic, as it is far beyond a Rangebringer in terms of difficulty, and it doesn't exactly incite guild motivation and collaboration like the Cleric epic does. An epic pet won't help much in NToV from what I understand, but cleric noodles and ragebringers' sure will.<br>
<br>
  As for mages not getting snare, root, charm, mez, fear etc because it's never been &quot;what the class is about&quot;, I'm afraid the &quot;vision&quot; of class definition has been warped so much since the days of EQ's release it's not even funny.  Rogues, upon release, were never intended to be the ultimate damage dealing class--but since Verant could never really make disarm traps and picklock a skill of any great value, the &quot;Vision&quot; warped so that they would be &quot;assassins&quot; instead. I agree that mez, fear, charm are NOT what the mage is about.  But can you think of any uber ability a mage has in the age of Luclin that he should be penalized to the extent of not being able to handle a mob 25 levels lower if he/she doesnt have a pet out? How about a single add while soloing?  If you had asked me at lvl 50 pre-kunark, I would have laughed at the need of any damage mitigating/escape spells-- my damage output could not be matched by anyone, and I saw the lack of root to be a fair trade-off.  Now at 59 with mobs quadding for 150+, and a mages damage ability being middle of the road, yeah I'd like the equivalent to the lvl 1 druid root spell.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents<br>
<br>
Ycore Rixle<br>
