Ibudin 59th Necromancer of Immortal Mercy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mr Who needs a title?!</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/1/02 6:17:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1659.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Love for Mages...NOT</span><hr size=1> Maybe not level 1, but perhaps at a level when you can justify the pet owner having obtained a level of 'pet mastery'.  Just like we have to wait until level 35 to med with an open book.  Perhaps Mages should gain this ability at 39, Necros at 44, Beastlords, SKs, and other pet capable classes at 52.<br>
<br>
The same argument could (and should) be made for the AA skill for illusions lasting through zoning.  It's an inate ability that should start working after a certain level.  Probably around 20 when Enchanters get their last pre-Luclin racial illusions.  Necro at level 24 or 29.  Rogues and Bards at 45/49. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &ltFinal Destiny&gt</B></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uhalochanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HaloChanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Post-o-holic</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/1/02 6:26:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1659.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Love for Mages...NOT</span><hr size=1> 'Still quite powerful in grinding zones. Most mobs in Sebilis are sub 50, and still hit quite hard and have plenty of HP. '<br>
<br>
- Yes, but do you realize that when an enchanter actually gets this skill (can you say endless AA grinding, and needing to be 59).. then there won't be any need for them to be hanging around in seb? It will be a long time before more than little will get this skill, and I doubt when they're at the stage that they do get it, they'll want to hang around in zones with sub 50 mobs in. It doesn't remotely effect epic encounters, and yes perhaps groups, but like I said you won't see many enchanters in groups exp grinding with this, if at all. <br>
People often just think unfair when they hear 'perma charmed pet', well what about the VP stick with right click 49 charm? <br>
